GN is highly efficient in pushing outwards large amounts of ionised gas in\nour targets. The mechanical outflow luminosities for WISSH quasars correspond\nto higher fractions (~1-3%) of L_Bol than those derived for lower L_Bol AGN.\nOur targets host very massive (M_BH>~2x10^9 M_Sun) black holes which are still\naccreting at a high rate (i.e. a factor of ~0.4-3 of the Eddington limit).\nThese findings demonstrate that WISSH quasars offer the opportunity of probing\nthe extreme end of both luminosity and SMBH mass functions and revealing\npowerful ionised outflows able to affect the evolution of their host galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Dec 2016 15:00:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-15"}
